",["$r","Intro",null,{"children":[["$r","p",null,{"children":["As we shared in the ",["$r","a",null,{"href":"/blog/2022/03/29/react-v18","children":"release post"}],", React 18 introduces features powered by our new concurrent renderer, with a gradual adoption strategy for existing applications. In this post, we will guide you through the steps for upgrading to React 18."]}],["$r","p",null,{"children":["Please ",["$r","a",null,{"href":"https://github.com/facebook/react/issues/new/choose","target":"_blank","rel":"nofollow noopener noreferrer","children":"report any issues"}]," you encounter while upgrading to React 18."]}]]}],"
",["$r","Note",null,{"children":["$r","p",null,{"children":["For React Native users, React 18 will ship in a future version of React Native. This is because React 18 relies on the New React Native Architecture to benefit from the new capabilities presented in this blogpost. For more information, see the ",["$r","a",null,{"href":"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FZ0cG47msEk&t=1530s","target":"_blank","rel":"nofollow noopener noreferrer","children":"React Conf keynote here"}],"."]}]}],"
